---
description: Define a cinematic motion system with consistent animation language
globs: ["components/**/*", "app/**/*"]
alwaysApply: true
---

## MOTION PHILOSOPHY

- Motion must feel intentional, cinematic, and premium
- Every animation should have purpose and hierarchy
- Avoid randomness — define a consistent motion language

## TIMING SYSTEM

- Fast: 0.2s – micro interactions
- Medium: 0.4–0.6s – UI transitions
- Slow: 0.8–1.2s – hero / page animations

## EASING SYSTEM

- Default: power2.out
- Entrance: power3.out
- Dramatic: expo.out
- Never use linear easing

## ENTRANCE PATTERNS

- Fade + translate (y: 20–60)
- Stagger children elements
- Animate opacity + transform only

## SCROLL SYSTEM

- Use ScrollTrigger with restraint
- Prefer reveal-on-scroll over constant animation
- Avoid scroll fatigue

## LAYERING

- Use depth:
  - Background (slow movement)
  - Mid layer (normal)
  - Foreground (interactive)

## PARALLAX

- Subtle only (never extreme)
- Different speeds for depth illusion

## RULE

Motion should feel like a film, not a website.
